1
00:01:35,228 --> 00:01:36,362
Zhou Xiaofeng.

2
00:01:37,030 --> 00:01:38,398
Performance pressure is intense now.

3
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,400
When interests are involved,

4
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:42,936
then indications

5
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:44,571
and contraindications

6
00:01:45,071 --> 00:01:45,872
can become

7
00:01:47,073 --> 00:01:48,007
very subtle.

8
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:06,793
In the race for Heart Center director,

9
00:02:07,393 --> 00:02:08,294
you have to fight with your back to the wall.

10
00:02:09,128 --> 00:02:10,230
I'm doing all this for you.

11
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,165
The center director

12
00:02:12,632 --> 00:02:13,933
will have authority over

13
00:02:13,933 --> 00:02:15,568
the personnel and finances

14
00:02:16,402 --> 00:02:17,604
of several departments under the center.

15
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:19,172
If Sheng Nian

16
00:02:19,239 --> 00:02:20,640
really becomes Heart Center director,

17
00:02:21,574 --> 00:02:22,642
he'll be able to directly decide

18
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:23,877
Cardiology's personnel appointments

19
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:24,944
and performance-bonus distribution.

20
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:26,613
Then Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery

21
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:28,047
will never truly cooperate again.

22
00:02:31,184 --> 00:02:31,918
These two patients

23
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:34,153
are completely willing to have the surgery.

24
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:37,023
Even if someone questions us afterward,

25
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:37,824
we can still

26
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:38,958
produce the guidelines.

27
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:40,226
We'd be on solid ground.

28
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,084
Why are you here?

29
00:03:05,718 --> 00:03:06,486
I came to see you.

30
00:03:06,886 --> 00:03:07,287
Sit.

31
00:03:13,993 --> 00:03:15,695
I heard your one-stop treatment program

32
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:17,397
is really taking off.

33
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:20,033
Thanks to your promotional resources.

34
00:03:26,172 --> 00:03:27,240
By the way, there's a patient

35
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:28,675
named Shen Shuxian, right?

36
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:30,343
I've arranged everything.

37
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:31,211
Don't worry.

38
00:03:31,444 --> 00:03:32,478
I'll operate personally when the time comes.

39
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:36,015
That's why I'm here too.

40
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,184
Why not try

41
00:03:38,284 --> 00:03:39,252
medication first?

42
00:03:39,686 --> 00:03:40,753
She doesn't have any contraindication

43
00:03:40,853 --> 00:03:41,921
to long-term anticoagulation, does she?

44
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:44,891
I asked Director Guo.

45
00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:46,159
He said the patient's family

46
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:47,493
strongly requested surgery.

47
00:03:50,997 --> 00:03:52,532
From what I understand,

48
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:54,434
they seem to view

49
00:03:54,534 --> 00:03:55,568
oral anticoagulants

50
00:03:55,602 --> 00:03:56,703
as something terrifying,

51
00:03:57,437 --> 00:03:58,404
as if taking them

52
00:03:58,504 --> 00:04:00,073
will immediately cause a fatal brain hemorrhage.

53
00:04:03,209 --> 00:04:04,010
What are you trying to say?

54
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,591
Shen Shuxian's bleeding

55
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:19,926
risk score isn't high.

56
00:04:20,193 --> 00:04:21,327
It's completely different

57
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:22,795
from Qiangwei's previous case.

58
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:24,163
So

59
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,865
I don't think you can

60
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:28,034
use the fact that surgery isn't inferior to medication

61
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:29,569
to steer a patient toward

62
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:30,837
an operation costing hundreds

63
00:04:30,903 --> 00:04:32,305
or even thousands of times more.

64
00:04:33,172 --> 00:04:34,507
Oral medication

65
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,009
costs only a few hundred yuan a year.

66
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,276
But this one-stop procedure

67
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,144
costs over a hundred thousand.

68
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:40,346
Even with reimbursement,

69
00:04:40,847 --> 00:04:42,015
they'll still pay tens of thousands.

70
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:43,616
The patient clearly

71
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:44,484
wants the operation.

72
00:04:45,051 --> 00:04:45,885
The process is clear.

73
00:04:46,886 --> 00:04:47,754
What's the problem?

74
00:04:48,354 --> 00:04:49,188
You and I both know

75
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:50,923
medicine has high barriers

76
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:51,758
and a major information gap.

77
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:53,192
As doctors,

78
00:04:53,593 --> 00:04:54,093
if our wording leans

79
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,295
even slightly one way,

80
00:04:55,361 --> 00:04:56,262
we can guide patients

81
00:04:56,362 --> 00:04:57,196
toward the decision

82
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:57,830
we want them to make.

83
00:04:59,132 --> 00:04:59,766
Especially

84
00:04:59,766 --> 00:05:00,933
when financial interests are driving it.

85
00:05:02,935 --> 00:05:03,202
Fine.

86
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,405
You have a point.

87
00:05:06,172 --> 00:05:06,673
Director Ouyang,

88
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:07,807
why don't you take this seat instead?

89
00:05:10,743 --> 00:05:12,011
That's not what I meant.

90
00:05:12,612 --> 00:05:13,680
I just came to ask

91
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,947
whether you really think

92
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:15,882
this surgery is necessary.

93
00:05:16,049 --> 00:05:16,983
She's your acquaintance.

94
00:05:17,116 --> 00:05:18,051
If you don't want her operated on,

95
00:05:18,117 --> 00:05:18,785
then don't do it.

96
00:05:19,252 --> 00:05:20,386
Simple. No problem.

97
00:05:21,521 --> 00:05:21,988
I know.

98
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:22,889
I know you're under

99
00:05:22,889 --> 00:05:23,823
all kinds of pressure right now.

100
00:05:24,290 --> 00:05:24,791
This one-stop program

101
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,092
really did open up the situation for you.

102
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:27,727
But you can't just

103
00:05:27,794 --> 00:05:28,928
disregard your patients like this.

104
00:05:29,195 --> 00:05:30,430
How am I disregarding them?

105
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:32,031
I asked Director Guo.

106
00:05:32,331 --> 00:05:33,199
You asked Director Guo.

107
00:05:33,266 --> 00:05:33,733
But did you personally

108
00:05:33,766 --> 00:05:34,867
look into the case?

109
00:05:35,201 --> 00:05:35,868
Or did you simply choose

110
00:05:35,968 --> 00:05:37,103
to turn a blind eye?

111
00:05:38,104 --> 00:05:38,671
So you came today

112
00:05:38,671 --> 00:05:39,572
just to question me?

113
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:41,874
To accuse me of overtreatment

114
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:43,242
and exploiting patients?

115
00:05:43,242 --> 00:05:44,077
I'm not questioning you.

116
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:45,044
I trust you.

117
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:46,879
Is this what trust looks like?

118
00:05:48,881 --> 00:05:50,316
In what capacity are you questioning me?

119
00:05:52,552 --> 00:05:54,487
An ex-girlfriend? A sales manager?

120
00:05:55,888 --> 00:05:56,322
Fine.

121
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:57,790
Then just treat me

122
00:05:57,924 --> 00:05:59,092
as a sales manager.

123
00:06:00,159 --> 00:06:00,993
I only want to ask one thing:

124
00:06:00,993 --> 00:06:01,794
is this how

125
00:06:01,994 --> 00:06:03,629
a department chief should behave?

126
00:06:04,163 --> 00:06:04,997
Where is your bottom line?

127
00:06:05,932 --> 00:06:07,033
Where did it go?

128
00:06:13,005 --> 00:06:14,173
If you're done, you can leave.

129
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:28,321
Patients are already pitiful enough when they're sick.

130
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:28,955
The door's there.

131
00:06:40,466 --> 00:06:41,534
You're worried that their

132
00:06:41,634 --> 00:06:42,935
one-stop atrial fibrillation procedures

133
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:44,303
amount to overtreatment,

134
00:06:45,471 --> 00:06:46,372
and that Zhou Xiaofeng

135
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:47,640
is turning a blind eye.

136
00:06:48,307 --> 00:06:48,841
Yes.

137
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:50,643
I thought

138
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:51,744
he would control it strictly.

139
00:06:52,044 --> 00:06:53,012
But after talking to him,

140
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:53,946
I'm not so sure anymore.

141
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,681
So I wanted you to persuade him.

142
00:06:56,115 --> 00:06:56,949
What does this have to do with you?

143
00:07:00,887 --> 00:07:01,888
It's all Cardiology business.

144
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:02,722
How am I supposed to persuade him?

145
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:05,491
Besides you and Dr. Fang,

146
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:06,692
I can't think of anyone else

147
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:07,593
who could get through to him.

148
00:07:08,327 --> 00:07:09,362
Then go ask Dr. Fang.

149
00:07:10,062 --> 00:07:10,997
I hope you don't think

150
00:07:11,063 --> 00:07:12,165
I'm meddling.

151
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:13,966
I'm genuinely worried about Director Zhou.

152
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:15,868
I know

153
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:17,303
this one-stop treatment

154
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:19,105
really has helped him gain momentum,

155
00:07:19,572 --> 00:07:20,573
but I'm even more worried

156
00:07:20,673 --> 00:07:22,375
it may end up hurting him.

157
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,174
Did you know

158
00:07:55,174 --> 00:07:55,708
what Director Guo was doing?

159
00:08:04,550 --> 00:08:05,351
This hurts, doesn't it?

160
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:21,934
Is it worth it?

161
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:26,839
For a center-director position,

162
00:08:36,115 --> 00:08:36,682
results,

163
00:08:37,583 --> 00:08:38,251
bonuses,

164
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:39,952
and beds.

165
00:08:42,388 --> 00:08:43,389
If you keep going like this,

166
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,725
you'll become just like

167
00:08:45,791 --> 00:08:46,325
Director Sheng, the man you criticize.

168
00:08:50,563 --> 00:08:51,597
Our positions are different.

169
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,433
What I say probably won't matter.

170
00:08:56,168 --> 00:08:57,403
You must have your own considerations.

171
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:00,907
But the Zhou Xiaofeng I know

172
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:03,209
may be old-fashioned,

173
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:05,278
stubborn,

174
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:07,813
and completely humorless,

175
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:11,083
but he's the good partner I chose,

176
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,490
and a good doctor devoted to patients.

177
00:09:40,713 --> 00:09:41,614
Whether or not you still see me

178
00:09:41,614 --> 00:09:42,515
as your brother,

179
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:44,116
I truly don't want

180
00:09:44,884 --> 00:09:45,885
to see you become

181
00:09:45,885 --> 00:09:46,752
someone I no longer recognize.

182
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:20,453
Uncle,

183
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,487
have you ever considered

184
00:10:21,687 --> 00:10:22,688
that they're trying to scare you?

185
00:10:23,356 --> 00:10:24,890
Overtreatment

186
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:25,825
is rampant now.

187
00:10:26,092 --> 00:10:26,492
Look,

188
00:10:26,926 --> 00:10:27,827
this hospital

189
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:28,995
built all these buildings.

190
00:10:29,495 --> 00:10:31,230
Doctors and nurses

191
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,131
all have to be paid, right?

192
00:10:32,398 --> 00:10:33,432
Where does that money come from?

193
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:34,533
It all comes from

194
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,634
you patients.

195
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,503
And now they're pushing some one-stop treatment.

196
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:38,838
I looked it up online.

197
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:39,972
Hospitals are using you

198
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,374
as guinea pigs,

199
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:43,242
just to increase

200
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,677
their revenue and performance.

201
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:45,077
Uncle.

202
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:46,245
Nonsense.

203
00:10:46,712 --> 00:10:47,647
Who are you calling nonsensical?

204
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:48,214
You're being sold out

205
00:10:48,214 --> 00:10:48,648
and still counting the money for them.

206
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,615
You're talking nonsense.

207
00:10:49,949 --> 00:10:50,449
Let me tell you,

208
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,384
I don't know about others,

209
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:51,984
but Director Zhou

210
00:10:52,118 --> 00:10:53,319
isn't that kind of person.

211
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:53,919
Don't point at me. You—

212
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:54,587
So what if I point?

213
00:10:54,587 --> 00:10:55,321
Who are you?

214
00:10:55,654 --> 00:10:56,455
Who are you?

215
00:10:56,555 --> 00:10:57,490
You're grabbing an old man?

216
00:10:57,523 --> 00:10:57,990
Who do you think you are?

217
00:10:58,524 --> 00:10:58,958
Nurse!

218
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:00,026
Nurse!

219
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:01,127
Something's wrong.

220
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:02,294
People are fighting in our ward.

221
00:11:02,361 --> 00:11:02,928
Go take a look.

222
00:11:10,036 --> 00:11:10,269
Hello?

223
00:11:11,103 --> 00:11:11,604
Director Zhou.

224
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:12,838
Factory Director Ma

225
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:14,173
got into a fight with someone in the ward.

226
00:11:15,107 --> 00:11:15,508
What?

227
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:16,609
Xiaojing went over to handle it.

228
00:11:17,043 --> 00:11:18,210
Do you want to come take a look too?

229
00:11:20,646 --> 00:11:21,047
Old Lu,

230
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,548
don't mind me getting worked up.

231
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:24,683
I've got a little umbrella in here too.

232
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:25,317
I can hold out.

233
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:26,552
Just think about

234
00:11:27,286 --> 00:11:28,754
that mass-poisoning incident in our village.

235
00:11:29,588 --> 00:11:30,356
Everyone,

236
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:31,590
young and old, was drinking happily.

237
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:33,125
Then suddenly people started collapsing.

238
00:11:33,592 --> 00:11:34,827
The whole courtyard was full of people on the ground.

239
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:35,795
I'm telling you,

240
00:11:35,795 --> 00:11:37,329
my legs went weak with fear.

241
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:38,431
Director Zhou

242
00:11:38,764 --> 00:11:39,598
led the medical team

243
00:11:39,632 --> 00:11:40,566
and rushed straight over.

244
00:11:41,133 --> 00:11:42,868
They were like soldiers sent from heaven.

245
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:43,502
And while they were at it,

246
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:45,204
they even saved my aunt

247
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,472
when she had a stroke.

248
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:47,907
That whole afternoon,

249
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:49,742
even the King of Hell must've been confused.

250
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:52,278
People kept arriving

251
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:53,612
at the gates of his palace.

252
00:11:54,013 --> 00:11:55,014
They'd go in,

253
00:11:55,281 --> 00:11:56,215
then somehow walk

254
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,450
right back out again.

255
00:11:58,284 --> 00:11:59,719
A major hospital like this,

256
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:00,786
and a senior director,

257
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,354
using

258
00:12:02,488 --> 00:12:03,722
their own weekend

259
00:12:04,090 --> 00:12:05,991
to travel all the way to the countryside

260
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:08,027
and treat people for free.

261
00:12:08,627 --> 00:12:09,595
What would they have to gain?

262
00:12:10,529 --> 00:12:12,064
My finances aren't good,

263
00:12:12,765 --> 00:12:14,266
so they recommended

264
00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:15,935
the cheaper occluder.

265
00:12:16,836 --> 00:12:17,870
They said

266
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:19,004
there's also

267
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:20,973
a biodegradable occluder.

268
00:12:21,607 --> 00:12:21,907
That's right.

269
00:12:22,475 --> 00:12:23,309
Our hospital has it too.

270
00:12:23,542 --> 00:12:24,443
If you want one,

271
00:12:24,443 --> 00:12:25,044
you certainly can have it.

272
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:27,012
But personally, I don't think it's necessary.

273
00:12:27,279 --> 00:12:28,280
The biodegradable occluder

274
00:12:28,314 --> 00:12:29,682
costs several times more than the metal one.

275
00:12:30,516 --> 00:12:31,951
And for your condition,

276
00:12:32,284 --> 00:12:33,152
the metal occluder

277
00:12:33,352 --> 00:12:34,386
works just as well.

278
00:12:34,887 --> 00:12:36,288
If he were only trying to make money,

279
00:12:36,455 --> 00:12:36,922
would he do that?

280
00:12:38,124 --> 00:12:39,091
He truly

281
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,293
cares about ordinary people.

282
00:12:42,027 --> 00:12:43,129
After everything he's done

283
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:43,963
for us,

284
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:45,731
ma'am,

285
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:49,468
if we still say he has bad intentions,

286
00:12:49,902 --> 00:12:50,236
then

287
00:12:50,636 --> 00:12:52,371
are there any good people left in this world?

288
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,050
I know.

289
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:06,152
I know you're under

290
00:13:06,185 --> 00:13:06,886
all kinds of pressure right now.

291
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:07,887
This one-stop program

292
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,121
really did open up the situation for you.

293
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:10,689
But you can't just

294
00:13:10,689 --> 00:13:11,924
disregard your patients like this.

295
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,492
How am I disregarding them?

296
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:15,127
I asked Director Guo.

297
00:13:15,327 --> 00:13:16,529
You asked Director Guo.

298
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,330
But did you personally look into it?

299
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:19,598
Or did you simply choose

300
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,866
to turn a blind eye?

301
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:23,903
Results.

302
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:25,371
Bonuses.

303
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:27,072
Beds.

304
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:28,974
If you keep going like this,

305
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:30,943
you'll become just like

306
00:13:31,076 --> 00:13:31,610
Director Sheng, the man you criticize.

307
00:13:33,679 --> 00:13:34,947
But the Zhou Xiaofeng I know

308
00:13:35,514 --> 00:13:36,282
may be old-fashioned,

309
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:37,516
stubborn,

310
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:39,151
and completely humorless,

311
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:41,887
but he's the good partner I chose,

312
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:44,390
and a good doctor devoted to patients.

313
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:25,998
Before, you doctors

314
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:27,066
all said I should have surgery.

315
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:29,268
Now you're saying we need to reconsider.

316
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:30,502
Why do you keep changing your minds

317
00:14:30,636 --> 00:14:31,804
and never give us a clear answer?

318
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:32,805
Exactly, doctor.

319
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:34,073
Didn't we agree before

320
00:14:34,073 --> 00:14:34,807
that I'd have surgery?

321
00:14:34,974 --> 00:14:35,774
Why are you suddenly saying

322
00:14:35,808 --> 00:14:36,709
I shouldn't?

323
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:37,910
As I just explained,

324
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:39,845
the surgery itself is invasive

325
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:40,546
and carries risks.

326
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:41,880
We should still be cautious.

327
00:14:42,248 --> 00:14:42,681
Dr. Zhou,

328
00:14:42,948 --> 00:14:43,849
you mean

329
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:45,351
we should go home and take medication first?

330
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:45,884
Yes.

331
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:46,719
After you go home,

332
00:14:46,752 --> 00:14:47,920
take the medication strictly as prescribed

333
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:48,888
and come back for regular follow-ups.

334
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:50,623
Even if medication doesn't work well,

335
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:52,524
there will still be time for surgery later.

336
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:54,526
Right. Listen to the doctor.

337
00:14:54,793 --> 00:14:55,494
See?

338
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:56,829
Listen to the doctor.

339
00:14:56,996 --> 00:14:57,997
Go home and take the medicine.

340
00:14:59,598 --> 00:15:00,199
Head nurse,

341
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,369
we've decided not to have surgery.

342
00:15:04,503 --> 00:15:05,437
They're not having it either.

343
00:15:05,971 --> 00:15:06,906
We'll go home and take medication.

344
00:15:07,773 --> 00:15:08,807
For all patients scheduled

345
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:09,708
for elective one-stop treatment,

346
00:15:09,842 --> 00:15:10,843
run another round

347
00:15:11,143 --> 00:15:12,344
of screening.

348
00:15:13,279 --> 00:15:13,679
Okay.

349
00:15:15,114 --> 00:15:15,648
Director Zhou,

350
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:19,051
you truly are rare.

351
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,147
Off work?

352
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:51,583
I want to apologize.

353
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:56,055
In what capacity

354
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,256
should I accept your apology?

355
00:15:57,990 --> 00:15:59,024
You're a department chief.

356
00:15:59,391 --> 00:16:00,592
I'm only a lowly sales rep.

357
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:01,927
You could crush me

358
00:16:01,994 --> 00:16:02,928
with one finger.

359
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:04,964
Director Zhou, you're overthinking it.

360
00:16:05,364 --> 00:16:06,065
No apology is necessary.

361
00:16:52,411 --> 00:16:52,911
I'm sorry.

362
00:16:54,813 --> 00:16:56,081
I shouldn't have spoken like that that day.

363
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:02,454
Shen Shuxian's family

364
00:17:02,488 --> 00:17:03,288
told you everything, right?

365
00:17:09,795 --> 00:17:10,596
Lately, I really have

366
00:17:11,964 --> 00:17:12,765
been a little out of control.

367
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:15,868
You ignored your sales targets and came to warn me.

368
00:17:17,269 --> 00:17:18,504
Thank you for hitting the brakes for me.

369
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,241
What can I say? I'm foolish.

370
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:23,876
I knew I'd offend you,

371
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:25,744
yet I still had to challenge the wrong person.

372
00:17:26,945 --> 00:17:28,213
You're still the same Ouyang.

373
00:17:29,448 --> 00:17:30,249
I'm lucky to have you.

374
00:17:42,694 --> 00:17:43,529
Doesn't this look like me?

375
00:17:45,197 --> 00:17:47,166
A tiny official, always putting on airs.

376
00:17:48,534 --> 00:17:49,968
Next time I make you angry,

377
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:52,404
crush it with one finger.

378
00:17:59,111 --> 00:17:59,678
If

379
00:17:59,878 --> 00:18:01,046
that still isn't enough,

380
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:02,815
use this.

381
00:18:03,882 --> 00:18:04,783
Squeeze it to death.

382
00:18:10,289 --> 00:18:11,356
It's not as cute as these.

383
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:17,763
What's this?

384
00:18:23,802 --> 00:18:24,470
Manager Ouyang,

385
00:18:25,704 --> 00:18:26,472
would you do me the honor

386
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:27,573
of having dinner with me?

387
00:18:28,974 --> 00:18:29,808
I'm starving.

388
00:18:32,077 --> 00:18:32,744
Sister Xia's place.

389
00:18:56,368 --> 00:18:57,102
What are you doing?

390
00:18:57,769 --> 00:18:58,670
Why are you using the back door?

391
00:18:58,971 --> 00:18:59,705
Do you know what period we're in?

392
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:01,807
The director election is imminent.

393
00:19:01,874 --> 00:19:02,875
My position is so sensitive.

394
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:04,710
Director Sheng's office door is open.

395
00:19:04,710 --> 00:19:05,811
If he sees me coming to you,

396
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:06,745
I'll become a traitor.

397
00:19:06,845 --> 00:19:07,880
Aren't you overthinking it?

398
00:19:08,847 --> 00:19:09,615
What exactly are you here for?

399
00:19:11,016 --> 00:19:11,683
I came to see

400
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:13,252
the good partner I know.

401
00:19:14,253 --> 00:19:14,953
I heard

402
00:19:14,953 --> 00:19:16,455
he suspended the one-stop clinic.

403
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,825
A thumbs-up for Cardiology's little whirlwind.

404
00:19:23,428 --> 00:19:25,230
Don't you still owe me something?

405
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:33,805
It's not that hard to say, is it?

406
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:34,806
Director Zhou.

407
00:19:43,048 --> 00:19:44,583
You're welcome, Little Whirlwind.

408
00:20:00,065 --> 00:20:00,832
Seriously?

409
00:20:00,966 --> 00:20:01,433
I never expected

410
00:20:01,466 --> 00:20:03,635
Director Zhou to have such a romantic past.

411
00:20:06,505 --> 00:20:07,606
When Director Zhou was young...

412
00:20:07,606 --> 00:20:08,073
Director Zhou.

413
00:20:08,407 --> 00:20:09,608
He was quite handsome then.

414
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,475
He's even more handsome now.

415
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:12,411
He kind of looks like...

416
00:20:12,477 --> 00:20:13,512
He was a fresh-faced heartthrob back then.

417
00:20:14,313 --> 00:20:15,213
It seems to be from university.

418
00:20:15,447 --> 00:20:15,881
The woman beside him

419
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:16,648
is pretty too.

420
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:18,884
Who are you talking about?

421
00:20:19,084 --> 00:20:19,484
Dr. Fang.

422
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:20,786
Someone just posted an article

423
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:21,853
about Director Zhou in the group chat.

424
00:20:22,654 --> 00:20:22,988
Look.

425
00:20:26,091 --> 00:20:27,326
Director Zhou was handsome when he was young.

426
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:40,072
Hello?

427
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:41,607
Did you see the post?

428
00:20:42,641 --> 00:20:43,041
I did.

429
00:20:43,675 --> 00:20:44,743
It may be inconvenient for you,

430
00:20:44,943 --> 00:20:45,944
so how about I write a post

431
00:20:46,111 --> 00:20:46,912
to clarify things?

432
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:48,947
Clarify what?

433
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:51,483
Everything in the post is true.

434
00:20:59,091 --> 00:20:59,958
No matter what,

435
00:21:00,158 --> 00:21:01,026
for a post like this

436
00:21:01,126 --> 00:21:01,927
to appear at this moment

437
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:03,028
is suspicious.

438
00:21:03,528 --> 00:21:04,196
And

439
00:21:04,496 --> 00:21:05,230
don't you think the writer

440
00:21:05,364 --> 00:21:06,632
was very deliberate?

441
00:21:07,199 --> 00:21:08,800
On the surface, it's all factual.

442
00:21:09,201 --> 00:21:10,369
But between the lines,

443
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:12,237
it leaves endless room for speculation.

444
00:21:13,205 --> 00:21:14,206
This is our private matter.

445
00:21:15,073 --> 00:21:16,241
And it happened so long ago.

446
00:21:16,908 --> 00:21:18,043
We don't owe anyone an explanation.

447
00:21:18,844 --> 00:21:19,878
If hospital leadership asks,

448
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,413
I'll tell them the truth.

449
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:22,547
It's fine.

450
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:25,651
Don't worry.

451
00:21:51,309 --> 00:21:52,477
Dragging up gossip like this—

452
00:21:53,211 --> 00:21:54,046
how childish.

453
00:21:57,215 --> 00:21:57,949
Let them talk.

454
00:21:58,350 --> 00:21:59,551
Their mouths are on their own faces.

455
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:00,786
We can't control them.

456
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:02,521
But the point is,

457
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:03,388
this is happening right

458
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:04,723
at the critical moment of the center-director race.

459
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:06,725
It's a despicable tactic.

460
00:22:23,742 --> 00:22:25,010
The hospital really has to consider

461
00:22:25,143 --> 00:22:26,078
whether it can still

462
00:22:26,111 --> 00:22:26,611
entrust you with such responsibility.

463
00:22:26,611 --> 00:22:27,412
You said before

464
00:22:27,412 --> 00:22:28,513
that the Heart Center director position

465
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:29,414
was something

466
00:22:29,748 --> 00:22:30,515
you were determined to win.

467
00:22:31,049 --> 00:22:31,383
So am I.

468
00:22:31,383 --> 00:22:32,651
Does that mean it has to go to Director Sheng?

469
00:22:49,334 --> 00:22:49,835
Where are you?

470
00:22:53,305 --> 00:22:54,439
The election is tomorrow.

471
00:22:54,673 --> 00:22:55,574
How prepared are you?

472
00:22:58,043 --> 00:22:58,877
The presentation is done.

473
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:00,278
I've memorized the speech too.

474
00:23:01,012 --> 00:23:02,347
But knowing it's just a formality

475
00:23:02,481 --> 00:23:03,548
still makes me uncomfortable.

476
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:08,153
I know my chances are slim,

477
00:23:08,954 --> 00:23:10,122
but losing to him

478
00:23:10,756 --> 00:23:11,923
really doesn't sit right with me.

479
00:23:12,691 --> 00:23:13,692
What's there to resent?

480
00:23:14,126 --> 00:23:15,127
You deserve to lose.

481
00:23:16,128 --> 00:23:16,995
Let me break it down for you.

482
00:23:17,696 --> 00:23:18,463
In seniority,

483
00:23:19,264 --> 00:23:19,931
he outranks you, right?

484
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:22,434
Minus one point.

485
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:24,002
Resources:

486
00:23:25,303 --> 00:23:26,671
you don't do business outside the hospital.

487
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:28,840
Another point deducted.

488
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:30,976
Connections:

489
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:33,245
he's President Wang's former student.

490
00:23:33,678 --> 00:23:34,246
What are you?

491
00:23:36,882 --> 00:23:37,749
Appearance-wise,

492
00:23:42,354 --> 00:23:43,822
you have a slight edge.

493
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:46,224
But you've got conduct issues.

494
00:23:46,792 --> 00:23:47,726
That's a major taboo.

495
00:23:48,393 --> 00:23:49,594
What conduct issues do I have?

496
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:50,896
You're fooling around.

497
00:23:51,229 --> 00:23:52,130
Improper relations with women.

498
00:23:55,233 --> 00:23:55,934
You saw it too?

499
00:23:56,468 --> 00:23:57,302
I did.

500
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:59,004
Something that absurd...

501
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:01,706
Don't worry too much.

502
00:24:02,574 --> 00:24:03,308
In matters like this,

503
00:24:03,909 --> 00:24:05,410
the truth will clear your name in the end.

504
00:24:11,917 --> 00:24:12,851
Not entirely clean, though.

505
00:24:17,756 --> 00:24:18,623
I know

506
00:24:19,391 --> 00:24:20,525
you two dated.

507
00:24:21,126 --> 00:24:22,527
But that was so many years ago.

508
00:24:22,828 --> 00:24:23,995
Bringing it up now

509
00:24:24,596 --> 00:24:25,530
is pretty ridiculous.

510
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:28,133
I'm talking about now.

511
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,385
You're playing King Zhou again.

512
00:24:47,719 --> 00:24:48,753
What nonsense.

513
00:24:49,387 --> 00:24:50,455
Nothing happened between us.

514
00:24:52,290 --> 00:24:54,192
We just understand each other.

515
00:24:54,392 --> 00:24:55,961
You understand each other, but nothing happened?

516
00:24:56,628 --> 00:24:57,162
Nothing.

517
00:24:58,563 --> 00:25:00,065
We agreed to stop there.

518
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:01,733
It's just that I realized...

519
00:25:02,634 --> 00:25:03,034
I...

520
00:25:05,203 --> 00:25:06,304
You're finished, Zhou Xiaofeng.

521
00:25:06,905 --> 00:25:07,839
You're done for.

522
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:09,374
You've disappointed me so much.

523
00:25:09,407 --> 00:25:10,609
You're smitten.

524
00:25:11,243 --> 00:25:11,743
Tell me honestly.

525
00:25:11,910 --> 00:25:12,544
When did it happen?

526
00:25:14,613 --> 00:25:15,313
New Year's Eve.

527
00:25:16,147 --> 00:25:17,582
The night you and Xiaoran broke up?

528
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:22,053
Your good brother was being dumped,

529
00:25:22,554 --> 00:25:23,321
and you were over there

530
00:25:23,321 --> 00:25:24,155
sharing a meeting of minds with someone?

531
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:25,590
How was I supposed to know

532
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:26,591
you two would break up?

533
00:25:27,225 --> 00:25:28,026
And the breakup

534
00:25:28,026 --> 00:25:28,960
was your own fault.

535
00:25:30,328 --> 00:25:30,896
Don't talk nonsense.

536
00:25:30,962 --> 00:25:31,930
What do you mean it was my fault?

537
00:25:32,063 --> 00:25:33,331
Just thinking about it makes me angry.

538
00:25:34,566 --> 00:25:35,000
What are you doing?

539
00:25:38,370 --> 00:25:38,870
Playing a game.

540
00:25:40,305 --> 00:25:40,805
A game?

541
00:25:41,406 --> 00:25:42,173
I'm going to ask you

542
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:42,841
a few questions.

543
00:25:43,408 --> 00:25:44,209
If you agree,

544
00:25:45,076 --> 00:25:45,810
take a drink.

545
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:47,612
My turn to ask.

546
00:25:49,915 --> 00:25:50,482
Do you remember

547
00:25:50,682 --> 00:25:51,449
what you said to me

548
00:25:51,516 --> 00:25:52,250
back then?

549
00:25:54,786 --> 00:25:55,487
I don't remember.

550
00:25:57,722 --> 00:25:59,524
You said you'd cherish Xiaoran,

551
00:26:00,825 --> 00:26:01,593
respect her,

552
00:26:01,893 --> 00:26:02,294
love her,

553
00:26:02,994 --> 00:26:03,728
and make her happy.

554
00:26:05,664 --> 00:26:06,398
Have you changed?

555
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:17,075
No. I haven't changed at all.

556
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,611
Then what are you doing?

557
00:26:20,478 --> 00:26:21,446
What exactly are you thinking?

558
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:22,681
What can I do?

559
00:26:22,847 --> 00:26:23,682
Does what I think even matter?

560
00:26:23,815 --> 00:26:24,983
I'm the one who got dumped.

561
00:26:28,987 --> 00:26:29,988
The person who initiated the breakup

562
00:26:31,690 --> 00:26:32,691
may not be any less miserable than you.

563
00:26:39,464 --> 00:26:40,231
What did she say to you?

564
00:26:43,134 --> 00:26:43,768
Your relationship

565
00:26:43,835 --> 00:26:44,502
is for the two of you to resolve.

566
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,205
But if

567
00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:48,406
you still care about her,

568
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:49,774
then hurry up.

569
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:10,161
What are you doing?

570
00:27:10,996 --> 00:27:11,696
Second question.

571
00:27:11,763 --> 00:27:12,931
Why do you have so many questions?

572
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:16,267
Who are you supporting in tomorrow's election?

573
00:27:16,868 --> 00:27:18,169
You just deducted so many points from me.

574
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:18,870
You're not really

575
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:19,904
planning to support Sheng Nian, are you?

576
00:27:27,112 --> 00:27:27,612
Don't you dare.

577
00:27:33,952 --> 00:27:34,686
You're crazy.

578
00:27:34,686 --> 00:27:35,920
Of course I'm supporting you.

579
00:27:36,087 --> 00:27:36,955
But what good does that do?

580
00:27:37,255 --> 00:27:37,989
I'm only one person.

581
00:27:38,189 --> 00:27:39,290
There are so many people in the Heart Center.

582
00:27:39,524 --> 00:27:40,725
Leadership makes the final decision anyway.

583
00:27:44,262 --> 00:27:45,463
Your vote is enough for me.

584
00:28:19,631 --> 00:28:21,466
Why are you still out so late?

585
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:23,435
Why are you taking a walk?

586
00:28:24,302 --> 00:28:26,071
Tomorrow is your big day.

587
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:28,606
You can't just give up.

588
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:30,608
Stay with me for a while.

589
00:28:30,675 --> 00:28:31,276
What's wrong?

590
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:35,814
It's been almost three years.

591
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:38,750
It's still the same sky of stars.

592
00:28:42,353 --> 00:28:43,354
But why do I feel

593
00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:47,158
we're getting farther and farther from our journey?

594
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:56,935
Humans are born of nature,

595
00:28:57,936 --> 00:28:58,670
and originate from the universe.

596
00:28:59,804 --> 00:29:00,405
Civilization is like

597
00:29:00,438 --> 00:29:01,439
the stars above us.

598
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:03,708
Birth, aging, illness, death,

599
00:29:03,842 --> 00:29:04,642
joy and sorrow, union and separation—

600
00:29:05,477 --> 00:29:06,745
all of it is insignificant before them.

601
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:08,480
Every individual's effort

602
00:29:10,115 --> 00:29:11,449
is one tiny point in this starry sky.

603
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:15,754
Our journey

604
00:29:16,721 --> 00:29:17,956
is toward the stars and the sea.

605
00:29:24,963 --> 00:29:26,197
The stars and the sea

606
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:31,202
were always far away.

607
00:29:37,876 --> 00:29:39,210
And you can only see the stars

608
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:40,311
when the weather is clear.

609
00:29:42,547 --> 00:29:43,715
What about

610
00:29:43,715 --> 00:29:44,149
when the weather is bad?

611
00:29:45,683 --> 00:29:46,785
Who guides us then?

612
00:29:51,523 --> 00:29:52,524
We can only rely on each other.

613
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:10,208
Not only that.

614
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,347
My brother told me

615
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:20,451
that when someone leaves this world,

616
00:30:22,921 --> 00:30:24,556
a new star appears in the sky.

617
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:28,993
They watch over us

618
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:31,863
and shine a light

619
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:32,864
for us as we walk through the night.

620
00:30:35,967 --> 00:30:36,734
As long as we want them there,

621
00:30:40,405 --> 00:30:41,306
the stars will always

622
00:30:41,372 --> 00:30:42,207
remain in our hearts.

623
00:31:22,013 --> 00:31:23,348
That concludes my detailed plan

624
00:31:23,648 --> 00:31:24,148
and proposal.

625
00:31:24,582 --> 00:31:25,650
This will both meet

626
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:27,051
the requirements for cost reduction and efficiency

627
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:28,052
and cut

628
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:28,987
unnecessary spending,

629
00:31:29,187 --> 00:31:30,321
while further refining

630
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:31,689
each subspecialty,

631
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:32,724
expanding its reach,

632
00:31:33,091 --> 00:31:34,959
and making it more precise and innovative.

633
00:31:35,193 --> 00:31:36,594
Clinical care, teaching, and research will advance together,

634
00:31:36,928 --> 00:31:38,029
ensuring Dongli Hospital's

635
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:38,863
Heart Center

636
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:40,765
remains firmly

637
00:31:40,999 --> 00:31:43,568
in Dongjiang's top tier for cardiovascular and cerebrovascular care.

638
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:44,769
Within three years,

639
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:47,672
we will compete for

640
00:31:48,273 --> 00:31:48,873
the top position in cardiac care across the province.

641
00:31:53,745 --> 00:31:54,245
Thank you.

642
00:32:01,953 --> 00:32:02,353
Everyone,

643
00:32:02,854 --> 00:32:03,955
Director Sheng has just

644
00:32:04,155 --> 00:32:05,423
used detailed data

645
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:07,625
to show us a future

646
00:32:07,959 --> 00:32:09,961
of significant performance growth

647
00:32:10,328 --> 00:32:12,230
and continued improvement in rankings.

648
00:32:12,463 --> 00:32:13,831
Next, let's invite

649
00:32:13,998 --> 00:32:14,565
Director Zhou

650
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:15,800
to share

651
00:32:16,167 --> 00:32:17,635
his vision

652
00:32:17,802 --> 00:32:18,836
and grand blueprint.

653
00:32:52,437 --> 00:32:53,037
Director Sheng,

654
00:32:55,473 --> 00:32:56,240
I disagree

655
00:32:57,041 --> 00:32:57,675
with your view.

656
00:33:05,950 --> 00:33:06,851
A Heart Center built around

657
00:33:07,085 --> 00:33:08,786
performance and rankings

658
00:33:09,387 --> 00:33:10,188
is not

659
00:33:10,254 --> 00:33:11,322
what I believe it should be.

660
00:33:17,595 --> 00:33:18,062
Last year,

661
00:33:20,031 --> 00:33:21,132
I returned from Guizhou

662
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:22,633
and competed for the position of Cardiology director,

663
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:24,302
full of ambition

664
00:33:26,204 --> 00:33:27,405
and determined to optimize...

665
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:28,706
Congratulations, partner.

666
00:33:29,007 --> 00:33:30,041
Your first battle is a victory.

667
00:33:30,274 --> 00:33:30,808
...reform...

668
00:33:30,875 --> 00:33:32,110
You're a lifesaver.

669
00:33:32,410 --> 00:33:33,144
...and benefit patients.

670
00:33:34,512 --> 00:33:35,313
But when I truly

671
00:33:35,413 --> 00:33:36,514
took that position,

672
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:38,449
I found a wall in front of me.

673
00:33:39,550 --> 00:33:40,318
It was called performance.

674
00:33:41,085 --> 00:33:42,286
As a department director,

675
00:33:42,453 --> 00:33:44,055
the first thing you have to consider

676
00:33:44,355 --> 00:33:45,189
is the department's development.

677
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:46,824
Your task now,

678
00:33:46,991 --> 00:33:47,925
I think, should be

679
00:33:48,226 --> 00:33:49,794
to increase revenue and reduce expenses.

680
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:52,363
After that,

681
00:33:52,463 --> 00:33:53,598
for a long time,

682
00:33:54,732 --> 00:33:55,466
I worked hard

683
00:33:56,601 --> 00:33:57,268
to become

684
00:33:57,368 --> 00:33:58,503
a qualified department director.

685
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,172
But gradually,

686
00:34:01,773 --> 00:34:03,007
I forgot that first,

687
00:34:03,174 --> 00:34:03,908
I should be a qualified doctor.

688
00:34:04,809 --> 00:34:05,276
Our department

689
00:34:05,309 --> 00:34:06,511
has too many elderly patients.

690
00:34:07,011 --> 00:34:08,679
They stay ten or more days and occupy beds.

691
00:34:09,247 --> 00:34:10,081
I think

692
00:34:10,748 --> 00:34:12,383
some patients shouldn't be admitted at all.

693
00:34:12,784 --> 00:34:13,551
Beds are so limited.

694
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:14,452
Of course they should be reserved

695
00:34:14,485 --> 00:34:15,286
for patients who need them more.

696
00:34:15,553 --> 00:34:16,587
Yu Aizhu was exactly

697
00:34:16,687 --> 00:34:17,722
one of those patients who needed us.

698
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:18,956
You asked Director Guo.

699
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:19,390
But did you personally

700
00:34:19,490 --> 00:34:20,558
look into it?

701
00:34:20,925 --> 00:34:22,160
Or did you choose

702
00:34:22,326 --> 00:34:23,428
to turn a blind eye to your subordinate?

703
00:34:27,031 --> 00:34:27,565
Not long ago,

704
00:34:28,266 --> 00:34:29,434
a family member asked me...

705
00:34:29,767 --> 00:34:30,201
Ms. Jiang,

706
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:32,470
today I'm here on behalf of the hospital

707
00:34:32,770 --> 00:34:33,771
to formally apologize to you.

708
00:34:34,772 --> 00:34:35,706
Regarding the dispute

709
00:34:35,773 --> 00:34:36,641
when Mr. Peng was admitted,

710
00:34:37,775 --> 00:34:39,110
the hospital did make mistakes.

711
00:34:39,811 --> 00:34:40,611
So no matter what,

712
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:43,114
we must convey our apology.

713
00:34:44,081 --> 00:34:44,682
I'm sorry.

714
00:34:47,952 --> 00:34:49,287
You say you represent the hospital.

715
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:52,523
But what about you, Director Zhou?

716
00:34:54,325 --> 00:34:55,493
As a patient's family member,

717
00:34:56,394 --> 00:34:57,995
I can fully feel

718
00:34:57,995 --> 00:34:58,796
how much care

719
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,631
and effort a doctor has given.

720
00:35:01,966 --> 00:35:02,867
So, Director Zhou,

721
00:35:03,568 --> 00:35:04,435
ask your conscience:

722
00:35:06,471 --> 00:35:07,705
did you truly do everything you could?

723
00:35:10,808 --> 00:35:12,510
Only now do I finally have an answer.

724
00:35:15,146 --> 00:35:15,713
I did not.

725
00:35:19,717 --> 00:35:20,985
I failed to fulfill

726
00:35:21,052 --> 00:35:21,786
my duty as a doctor.

727
00:35:24,922 --> 00:35:27,225
Somewhere along this road,

728
00:35:31,529 --> 00:35:32,363
I had already forgotten

729
00:35:32,396 --> 00:35:33,531
why I set out in the first place.

730
00:35:39,003 --> 00:35:39,637
But fortunately,

731
00:35:43,107 --> 00:35:43,774
I still remember

732
00:35:47,044 --> 00:35:47,912
all the faces

733
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:51,449
that accompanied me along the way.

734
00:35:56,487 --> 00:35:57,188
Those patients—

735
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:02,527
my patients.

736
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:05,863
Some were adorable

737
00:36:06,964 --> 00:36:07,465
and obedient.

738
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:09,967
Some loved causing trouble

739
00:36:11,602 --> 00:36:12,403
and had poor compliance.

740
00:36:14,038 --> 00:36:15,239
Some were cold at first

741
00:36:16,707 --> 00:36:17,608
and doubted everything.

742
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:19,243
Others chose

743
00:36:19,277 --> 00:36:20,444
to trust me unconditionally.

744
00:36:23,848 --> 00:36:24,815
Some were lonely.

745
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:29,287
Some were happy.

746
00:36:31,122 --> 00:36:32,190
Some I was able to save.

747
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:37,428
Others passed away in my care.

748
00:36:56,714 --> 00:36:57,882
They were all different,

749
00:36:59,050 --> 00:36:59,984
from every walk of life.

750
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:03,988
But it was precisely because of them

751
00:37:05,623 --> 00:37:06,724
that I became

752
00:37:06,791 --> 00:37:07,692
a true doctor.

753
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,127
They entrusted their lives

754
00:37:10,127 --> 00:37:10,962
to me.

755
00:37:11,796 --> 00:37:12,597
That trust was heavy.

756
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:14,532
It carried great weight.

757
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:16,667
Yet it also made my heart

758
00:37:16,767 --> 00:37:17,802
more grounded

759
00:37:18,035 --> 00:37:18,869
and stronger.

760
00:37:20,404 --> 00:37:21,038
My hands

761
00:37:22,006 --> 00:37:23,040
can still feel

762
00:37:23,174 --> 00:37:24,008
their heartbeats.

763
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:26,677
Because they are here,

764
00:37:27,612 --> 00:37:28,613
inside my heart,

765
00:37:29,914 --> 00:37:31,215
constantly reminding me

766
00:37:32,116 --> 00:37:33,251
to keep a clear conscience.

767
00:37:36,554 --> 00:37:37,255
If becoming

768
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,189
Heart Center director

769
00:37:39,490 --> 00:37:40,224
means turning

770
00:37:40,291 --> 00:37:41,392
those individual faces

771
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:42,893
into strings of numbers

772
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:43,928
on a performance report,

773
00:37:48,165 --> 00:37:48,966
I can't bear to do it.

774
00:37:52,703 --> 00:37:53,638
I can't let them go.

775
00:38:29,173 --> 00:38:29,974
Rather than that,

776
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:34,412
I'd rather return to being

777
00:38:36,213 --> 00:38:38,816
the stubborn, old-fashioned,

778
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:40,751
humorless

779
00:38:43,054 --> 00:38:44,622
Zhou Xiaofeng who puts patients first.

780
00:39:01,872 --> 00:39:02,473
Director Zhou,

781
00:39:07,078 --> 00:39:07,912
I want to thank you.

782
00:39:08,913 --> 00:39:10,715
Thank you for putting into words

783
00:39:10,815 --> 00:39:11,949
what, throughout my twenty-plus years of work,

784
00:39:12,016 --> 00:39:13,250
I've always wanted to say

785
00:39:13,984 --> 00:39:15,653
but never managed to express.

786
00:39:16,053 --> 00:39:16,887
Thank you very much.

787
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:17,955
Yes.

788
00:39:19,223 --> 00:39:20,224
Director Zhou is right.

789
00:39:20,791 --> 00:39:21,826
Performance evaluations

790
00:39:21,992 --> 00:39:23,527
should never come before patients.

791
00:39:24,095 --> 00:39:24,495
Agreed.

792
00:39:25,062 --> 00:39:25,930
I support Director Zhou.

793
00:39:26,230 --> 00:39:26,664
Exactly.

794
00:39:26,864 --> 00:39:27,932
We can't put the cart before the horse.

795
00:39:28,232 --> 00:39:29,467
We became doctors,

796
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:31,335
not accountants.

797
00:39:32,336 --> 00:39:33,070
Infectious Diseases agrees

798
00:39:33,104 --> 00:39:33,771
with Director Zhou.

799
00:39:33,971 --> 00:39:34,805
Count Anesthesiology in too.

800
00:39:35,005 --> 00:39:35,706
Laboratory Medicine agrees.

801
00:39:35,873 --> 00:39:37,241
Director, we support you.

802
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:38,242
We support the director.

803
00:39:38,476 --> 00:39:39,110
The Nursing Department

804
00:39:39,844 --> 00:39:40,845
supports Director Zhou.

805
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:44,882
We support Director Zhou.

806
00:40:34,732 --> 00:40:36,734
Thank you for supporting the hospital.

807
00:40:37,568 --> 00:40:39,303
A special thank-you to you, Old Ma.

808
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:39,870
You've worked hard.

809
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:57,488
When did you decide?

810
00:40:59,089 --> 00:41:00,424
I simply couldn't keep listening.

811
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,596
Wasn't that too impulsive?

812
00:41:06,263 --> 00:41:07,364
I thought it was great.

813
00:41:08,332 --> 00:41:10,000
Really handsome.

814
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:13,704
No matter what,

815
00:41:15,005 --> 00:41:16,073
you finally said

816
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:17,007
what you'd held in for so long.

817
00:41:18,042 --> 00:41:18,809
You must feel much better.

818
00:41:22,613 --> 00:41:23,013
Let's go.

819
00:41:26,884 --> 00:41:27,451
What did you think

820
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:28,085
of Director Zhou's speech?

821
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:30,921
What I think doesn't matter.

822
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:32,122
Leadership decides.

823
00:41:33,958 --> 00:41:36,727
But if you had to choose

824
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:38,095
between him and me

825
00:41:38,329 --> 00:41:39,797
for Heart Center director,

826
00:41:41,165 --> 00:41:41,632
who would you choose?

827
00:41:47,071 --> 00:41:47,872
Whoever would

828
00:41:48,472 --> 00:41:49,406
benefit patients more as director,

829
00:41:50,207 --> 00:41:50,908
is the one I'll support.

830
00:41:57,648 --> 00:41:58,883
The workstation in Qinghai

831
00:41:59,049 --> 00:41:59,750
has already been built.

832
00:42:00,117 --> 00:42:01,185
When are you planning to go?

833
00:42:01,952 --> 00:42:02,519
Tomorrow.

834
00:42:02,686 --> 00:42:03,521
I've arranged my schedule.

835
00:42:04,455 --> 00:42:05,923
Director Sheng is impressive.

836
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:07,491
He's acting as though nothing happened.

837
00:42:10,227 --> 00:42:11,762
Director Zhou may have won people's hearts,

838
00:42:11,962 --> 00:42:13,631
but the result is still uncertain.

839
00:42:21,438 --> 00:42:22,873
Thank you for still agreeing to see me.

840
00:42:22,873 --> 00:42:23,440
Ms. Jiang,

841
00:42:24,241 --> 00:42:25,509
a lot has happened recently.

842
00:42:26,477 --> 00:42:27,444
I've also thought a great deal.

843
00:42:28,245 --> 00:42:28,879
At the time,

844
00:42:30,047 --> 00:42:31,282
in treating Mr. Peng,

845
00:42:32,116 --> 00:42:33,250
I truly didn't do enough.

846
00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:37,688
Although this apology

847
00:42:38,188 --> 00:42:39,023
comes far too late,

848
00:42:40,524 --> 00:42:41,025
I...

849
00:42:44,828 --> 00:42:45,529
Ms. Jiang,

850
00:42:46,964 --> 00:42:47,431
I'm sorry.

851
00:42:51,802 --> 00:42:52,570
Director Zhou,

852
00:42:54,004 --> 00:42:55,105
being a doctor

853
00:42:55,873 --> 00:42:56,507
isn't easy, is it?
